==English==

===Etymology===
[[Category:Greek derivations]]
From [[Ancient Greek]] '''[[αυτοκρατής]]''' {{italbrac|autokrates}} “one who governs alone”, from '''[[αὐτός]]''' {{italbrac|autos}} “single, self, same, alone” + '''[[κράτος]]''' {{italbrac|kratos}} “power”.

===Noun===
'''autocracy'''

# form of [[government]] in which unlimited power is held by a single [[individual]]
[[Category:Government]]

